properties.description:
Array of message objects. Default shape: `{ id, text, senderId, userName, timestamp, attachments? }`. The `senderId` MUST match one of the `participants[].id` — this is how the chat decides whether a message is shown as 'own' (right-aligned) or 'other' (left-aligned). Example message:
```json
{
  "id": "msg-1",
  "text": "Hello!",
  "senderId": "user-1",
  "userName": "Alice",
  "timestamp": "2026-04-23T10:30:00Z",
  "attachments": [
    { "id": "f1", "name": "photo.png", "type": "image/png", "size": 204800, "url": "https://..." }
  ]
}
```
